54:03.66 ID:/LkvrVuw0\n\n山梨とかに登山にいくと無人駅でもSuicaタッチする場所用意してあるけどね\n\n離れるとわけわかんなくなっとるんだな\n\n39: 名無しさん＠恐縮です 2025/05/02(金) 17:56:46.56 ID:X3Mdgiaj0\n\nキセルだな\n\nキンコンは売れるの早かったから地方営業とかあんましたことないのか\n\n41: 名無しさん＠恐縮です 2025/05/02(金) 17:59:55.47 ID:XB9THq470\n\n使えないって車内でも駅でも放送しまくってるだろアホかよ\n\n42: 名無しさん＠恐縮です 2025/05/02(金) 18:01:01.10 ID:SbKYpPzD0\n\n子供の頃は切符買ってただろうに\n\n44: 名無しさん＠恐縮です 2025/05/02(金) 18:04:29.76 ID:v728JPRG0\n\n無人駅でもだいたいはスキャンするあの機械置いてるやろ\n\n45: 名無しさん＠恐縮です 2025/05/02(金) 18:05:59.11 ID:Bhz51FQi0\n\n>>44\n\n田舎の駅なめんな\n\n47: 名無しさん＠恐縮です 2025/05/02(金) 18:15:33.98 ID:hB9mAhbH0\n\n携帯で電話すればいいだろ\n\n50: 名無しさん＠恐縮です 2025/05/02(金) 18:17:05.49 ID:2jefwu7V0\n\n整理券と運転席の横にある運賃箱パターンのワンマン列車でなくて車掌のいる列車？\n\n車掌さんと話せばいいんじゃないの？\n\n52: 名無しさん＠恐縮です 2025/05/02(金) 18:19:07.54 ID:iMAz35QV0\n\nなんかバスが事故にあってしょうがなくその場で降りて歩いて帰ろうと当然バス代はただでいいって言われたんだがスイカはどうすればいいのか聞いたらそのままで大丈夫だって言われたことがある\n\n55: 名無しさん＠恐縮です 2025/05/02(金) 18:22:19.36 ID:q5emkLGM0\n\nなんでもsuicaに頼るからこうなる\n\n58: 名無しさん＠恐縮です 2025/05/02(金) 18:24:34.22 ID:7DpMvCu+0\n\nこれが言いたいためにわざわざ無人駅で降りたのかな？\n\n59: 名無しさん＠恐縮です 2025/05/02(金) 18:25:52.68 ID:utpTJSoH0\n\n降りる時にチェックされないんだ\n\n60: ハンター[Lv.44][木] 2025/05/02(金) 18:27:06.27 ID:OZq8Etuq0\n\nそよそもなにしにそこに鉄道使って行ったんだよ？\n\nプペル師匠ならそこまで車で送り迎えしてくれる権利を売ればいいだろ？\n\n68: 名無しさん＠恐縮です 2025/05/02(金) 18:35:12.90 ID:PEhKsAAs0\n\n>>60\n\n50プペ券を玄関で手渡してもらえる権利が売り出されてる\n\n62: 名無しさん＠恐縮です 2025/05/02(金) 18:28:31.43 ID:9ZavzCxM0\n\n券売機のところにインターホンあるんじゃないの\n\n65: 名無しさん＠恐縮です 2025/05/02(金) 18:33:27.91 ID:ZSlQR/Ck0\n\nそこまでして話題になりたいんだ\n\n69: 名無しさん＠恐縮です 2025/05/02(金) 18:35:41.87 ID:pGud66Bt0\n\n昔の定期の時は切符で入って定期で降りるキセルを\n\n何回かやると改札で止められるって聞いたな\n\n71: 名無しさん＠恐縮です 2025/05/02(金) 18:36:19.65 ID:FLKczjud0\n\n時間帯によってワンマン運転切り替わったりもするから、駅で中に車掌が居るからって聞いて乗ったら居なかったりする\n\n75: 名無しさん＠恐縮です 2025/05/02(金) 18:39:22.79 ID:DzmrM9UH0\n\n次にスイカ使う駅で説明して金払えばいいだけじゃん\n\n95: 名無しさん＠恐縮です 2025/05/02(金) 19:06:22.65 ID:VXvQJ2oG0\n\n詐欺れよ本業なんだから"}
{"topic": "Articles", "ss": "NewsApiFeeder", "ts": "2025-05-03T14:43:11Z", "url": "https://finance.yahoo.com/news/truist-financial-nyse-tfc-pay-144311222.html", "publishedAt": "2025-05-03T14:43:11Z", "content": "The board of Truist Financial Corporation (NYSE:TFC) has announced that it will pay a dividend of $0.52 per share on the 2nd of June. This makes the dividend yield 5.3%, which will augment investor r… [+3493 chars]", "title": "Truist Financial (NYSE:TFC) Will Pay A Dividend Of $0.52", "fullContent": "The board of Truist Financial Corporation (NYSE:TFC) has announced that it will pay a dividend of $0.52 per share on the 2nd of June. This makes the dividend yield 5.3%, which will augment investor returns quite nicely.\n\nTrump has pledged to \"unleash\" American oil and gas and these 15 US stocks have developments that are poised to benefit.\n\nTruist Financial's Payment Expected To Have Solid Earnings Coverage\n\nA big dividend yield for a few years doesn't mean much if it can't be sustained.\n\nHaving distributed dividends for at least 10 years, Truist Financial has a long history of paying out a part of its earnings to shareholders. Despite this history however, the company's latest earnings report actually shows that it didn't have enough earnings to cover its dividends. This is an alarming sign that could mean that Truist Financial's dividend at its current rate may no longer be sustainable for longer.\n\nOver the next 3 years, EPS is forecast to expand by 174.4%. The future payout ratio could be 49% over that time period, according to analyst estimates, which is a good look for the future of the dividend.\n\nNYSE:TFC Historic Dividend May 3rd 2025\n\nView our latest analysis for Truist Financial\n\nTruist Financial Has A Solid Track Record\n\nThe company has an extended history of paying stable dividends. The dividend has gone from an annual total of $0.96 in 2015 to the most recent total annual payment of $2.08. This means that it has been growing its distributions at 8.0% per annum over that time. The growth of the dividend has been pretty reliable, so we think this can offer investors some nice additional income in their portfolio.\n\nDividend Growth Potential Is Shaky\n\nThe company's investors will be pleased to have been receiving dividend income for some time. Unfortunately things aren't as good as they seem. Earnings per share has been sinking by 37% over the last five years. This steep decline can indicate that the business is going through a tough time, which could constrain its ability to pay a larger dividend each year in the future. However, the next year is actually looking up, with earnings set to rise. We would just wait until it becomes a pattern before getting too excited.\n\nThe Dividend Could Prove To Be Unreliable\n\nOverall, it's nice to see a consistent dividend payment, but we think that longer term, the current level of payment might be unsustainable. In the past the payments have been stable, but we think the company is paying out too much for this to continue for the long term. We would be a touch cautious of relying on this stock primarily for the dividend income."}
